# Shell scripts MUST use LF, always — they're embedded via go:embed and
# executed by bash (Claude Code / Codex / Cursor hooks, installers). A
# CRLF shebang line breaks bash at runtime ("$'\r': command not found"),
# and CRLF anywhere trips `case ... in`. Force LF regardless of a
# contributor's core.autocrlf setting so a Windows checkout can never
# commit CRLF into these files.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf

# PowerShell hooks are invoked by powershell.exe (CRLF-tolerant) but keep
# them LF for byte-stable go:embed + SHA-stamping across platforms.
*.ps1 text eol=lf

# Keep other line-ending-sensitive text stable.
*.go text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf

# Processor golden/parity fixtures are byte-compared — pin LF so a
# Windows checkout can't rewrite them to CRLF and break TestFilterGoldens.
internal/processors/testdata/** -text
